---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArchDiagram from '@/components/ArchDiagram.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="How It Works"
  description="Architecture walkthrough of the Configent config-driven agentic workflow engine."
>

  <div class="page container">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="page-label">Architecture</div>
      <h1>How it works</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Configent turns a YAML file into a fully operational RAG pipeline and
        agentic assistant. Here's what happens from config to response.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Diagram ──────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <ArchDiagram />
    </section>

    <!-- ── Step walkthrough ─────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>Step by step</h2>

      <div class="steps">

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">01</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Author a config</h3>
            <p>
              A solutions engineer writes a <code>config.yaml</code> that declares the client ID,
              knowledge base sources, active tools, agent model, and system prompt.
              No Python. No infrastructure decisions. This file is the entire integration spec.
            </p>
            <div class="code-block">
              <div class="cb-header">
                <span class="cb-dot r"></span>
                <span class="cb-dot a"></span>
                <span class="cb-dot g"></span>
                <span class="cb-filename">config.yaml</span>
              </div>
              <pre class="cb-pre"><code><span class="y-key">client_id</span>: <span class="y-str">acme-fab</span>
<span class="y-key">name</span>: <span class="y-str">Acme Fab Equipment</span>

<span class="y-key">branding</span>:
  <span class="y-key">logo</span>: <span class="y-str">assets/acme-fab/logo.svg</span>
  <span class="y-key">primary_color</span>: <span class="y-str">"#1B4F8A"</span>
  <span class="y-key">assistant_name</span>: <span class="y-str">AcmeAssist</span>

<span class="y-key">corpus</span>:
  <span class="y-key">source</span>: <span class="y-str">corpora/acme-fab/</span>
  <span class="y-key">chunking</span>:
    <span class="y-key">chunk_size</span>: <span class="y-num">800</span>
    <span class="y-key">overlap</span>: <span class="y-num">100</span>

<span class="y-key">agent</span>:
  <span class="y-key">model</span>: <span class="y-str">claude-sonnet-4-6</span>
  <span class="y-key">system_prompt_file</span>: <span class="y-str">prompts/acme-fab.md</span>
  <span class="y-key">max_tokens</span>: <span class="y-num">4096</span>
  <span class="y-key">effort</span>: <span class="y-str">medium</span>
  <span class="y-key">tools</span>:
    - <span class="y-str">search_docs</span>
    - <span class="y-str">get_document</span>
    - <span class="y-str">pricing_lookup</span>

<span class="y-key">limits</span>:
  <span class="y-key">rate_limit_per_minute</span>: <span class="y-num">20</span>
  <span class="y-key">daily_budget_usd</span>: <span class="y-num">2.00</span></code></pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">02</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Configent initialises the pipeline</h3>
            <p>
              On startup, the orchestration layer reads the config and:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Loads and embeds all knowledge base sources using <code>text-embedding-3-small</code></li>
              <li>Indexes embeddings into a client-isolated pgvector namespace</li>
              <li>Registers only the tools marked <code>enabled: true</code> — others are never loaded</li>
              <li>Builds the system prompt with the turn breakpoint for prompt cache optimisation</li>
            </ul>
            <p>
              Nothing is shared between clients. Each <code>client_id</code> gets an isolated
              vector store namespace, tool registry, and session state.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">03</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Queries run through the agent loop</h3>
            <p>
              When a user sends a message, it enters a manual agentic loop:
            </p>
            <ol>
              <li>Claude receives the conversation history + registered tool schemas</li>
              <li>If Claude calls a tool (e.g. <code>search_knowledge_base</code>), the engine executes it and appends the result</li>
              <li>The loop continues until Claude produces a final text response or <code>max_iterations</code> is reached</li>
              <li>Responses stream over SSE — text tokens and citation blocks arrive in real time</li>
            </ol>
            <p>
              The loop is deterministic and inspectable. Every tool call and result is logged,
              making it straightforward to debug or audit in enterprise contexts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-num">04</div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <h3>Response is delivered with citations</h3>
            <p>
              The final response streams to the frontend with inline citation popovers.
              Each cited passage maps back to a specific chunk in the knowledge base,
              with the source document and page number surfaced in the UI.
            </p>
            <p>
              This is not post-hoc attribution — citations are emitted as
              <code>search_result</code> blocks during tool execution and rendered
              by the client in real time.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ── Key design decisions ─────────────────────────────────── -->
    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key design decisions</h2>
      <div class="decision-grid">
        <div class="decision-card">
          <div class="dc-label">ADR-0001</div>
          <h4>Manual agent loop</h4>
          <p>
            Rather than delegating to a framework (LangChain, LlamaIndex), the agent loop
            is implemented explicitly. This gives full control over tool execution order,
            error handling, and streaming — all critical for enterprise reliability.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="decision-card">
          <div class="dc-label">ADR-0003</div>
          <h4>Prompt caching</h4>
          <p>
            The system prompt and knowledge base context are cached at a turn breakpoint.
            For clients with large, stable system prompts, this reduces cost and latency
            by up to 90% on cache hits.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="decision-card">
          <div class="dc-label">ADR-0002</div>
          <h4>pgvector for retrieval</h4>
          <p>
            Vector search runs in the same Postgres instance as the rest of the data.
            No separate vector DB to operate. Client namespaces are isolated by
            a <code>client_id</code> column — no cross-tenant leakage possible.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="decision-card">
          <div class="dc-label">ADR-0005</div>
          <h4>Config-driven tenancy</h4>
          <p>
            There is no code path per client. The orchestration layer reads the config
            at startup and builds everything from it. Adding a new client is a new file
            and a service restart — no deployment, no PR, no code review.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="page-nav">
      <a href={`${base}/demo`} class="page-nav-next">
        See it in action
        <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/>
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding-top: 4rem;
    padding-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .page-header {
    max-width: 64ch;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .page-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .page-header h1 { margin-bottom: 1rem; }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .section { margin-bottom: 4.5rem; }
  .section h2 { margin-bottom: 2rem; color: var(--text); }

  /* ── Steps ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .steps { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3rem; }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .step-num {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    opacity: 0.4;
    line-height: 1;
    padding-top: 0.2rem;
  }

  .step-body h3 { color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .step-body p  { color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 1rem; line-height: 1.7; }
  .step-body ul,
  .step-body ol { color: var(--text-muted); padding-left: 1.25rem; line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .step-body li { margin-bottom: 0.375rem; }

  /* ── Code block inside step ─────────────────────────────────── */
  .code-block {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .cb-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.375rem;
    padding: 0.625rem 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-elevated);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .cb-dot { width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%; }
  .cb-dot.r { background: #ff5f57; }
  .cb-dot.a { background: #ffbd2e; }
  .cb-dot.g { background: #28ca41; }

  .cb-filename {
    margin-left: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .cb-pre {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 0;
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  /* YAML tokens */
  .y-key  { color: var(--y-key); }
  .y-str  { color: var(--y-str); }
  .y-num  { color: var(--y-num); }
  .y-bool { color: var(--y-bool); }

  /* ── Decision grid ────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .decision-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .decision-card {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .dc-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .decision-card h4 { color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .decision-card p  { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.65; margin: 0; }

  /* ── Page nav ─────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-nav { display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; }

  .page-nav-next {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 0.625rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--accent);
    color: #fff;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .page-nav-next:hover { background: var(--accent-dim); text-decoration: none; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .step { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .step-num { font-size: 1.5rem; }
    .decision-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
